<DOC><DOCNO> AP881230-0001 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-30-88 0245EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-Bakkers-Television     12-30 0185</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Bakkers-Television,0189</SECOND><HEAD>Jim And Tammy Bakker Plan To Return To Television On Monday</HEAD><DATELINE>CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Jim and Tammy Bakker begin broadcasting anew television show from their living room Monday for at least sixindependent television stations across the nation, according to apublished report.   Bakker and three of his associates were indicted this month oncharges of misusing millions of dollars in PTL funds. Bakker couldnot be reached for comment Thursday.   The Charlotte Observer in Friday's editions quoted unidentifiedsources as saying that the live broadcasts from the Bakkers' livingroom near Pineville will be carried on stations in Albany, N.Y.;Atlanta; Chico, Calif.; Los Angeles; Philadelphia; and San Diego.   Bakker attorney Jim Toms of Hendersonville, N.C., said in atelephone interview Thursday night that the Bakkers had beenpreparing to return to television, but could not confirm when thereturn would take place.   Bakker has not had a regular TV show since he resigned from PTLin March 1987 after widely publicized allegations of his 1980 sexualencounter with church secretary Jessica Hahn and payments to keepher quiet.</TEXT></DOC>